# GENEVE (RFC 8926) over UDP/IPv4 port 6081, protocol type 0x0800 (IPv4), VNI 100, no options —
# tunneling a bare inner IPv4/ICMP packet (no inner Ethernet). Exercises the typed-tunnel dispatch:
# GENEVE's protocolType drives the ethertype demux to IPv4 (which accepts a 'geneve' parent), NOT the
# EthernetII fallback. source: standard GENEVE header + a real inner IP packet via UDP socket to
# 127.0.0.1:6081 on a debian:12 container's ethernet lo, captured with tcpdump.
